  "status": "current",
  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541164/rfm_PxrOSL.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=481&amp;height=655\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541164/rfm_PxrOSL.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"655\" data-width=\"481\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544541178\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfm_PxrOSL.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541164\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"85a6b687-6b33-46e0-93d9-33e99663883f\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541164/rfm_PxrOSL.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=481&amp;height=655 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541164/rfm_PxrOSL.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=481&amp;height=655 1x\"></span><p>The PxrOSL Pattern node is a useful way to create and prototype OSL patterns from inside Maya. It's excellent for playing around with options and controls.</p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"bbf8afc7-0a03-4352-8916-282a621df42e\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>We only support OSL patterns (textures for shading) and not closures (materials).</p></div></div><p>When you first open the node you'll see the representation above. If you expand the Source Code rollout you'll find a handy example built-in to the node.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541164/rfm_PxrOSLexampleSource.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=481&amp;height=817\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541164/rfm_PxrOSLexampleSource.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"817\" data-width=\"481\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544541181\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfm_PxrOSLexampleSource.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541164\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"b8ca9f77-65ab-4d6f-b952-523f9d0794eb\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541164/rfm_PxrOSLexampleSource.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=481&amp;height=817 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541164/rfm_PxrOSLexampleSource.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=481&amp;height=817 1x\"></span><p>You can see the source path under Compile and Reload buttons.</p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"617bc226-7a03-4508-8447-71e85663279d\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>The naming here is very important.</p><ul><li><p><code>shader sample_osl_pattern</code> is defined in the OSL Code.</p></li><li><p>The name defined in the OSL Code <em>must match</em> the name of the .osl Source File Path</p></li><li><p>The file path must be populated manually and must also match the name of the OSL Code with the compiled .oso extension</p></li></ul><p>If you fail to have the correct names you will get a warning and bad behavior.</p></div></div><p /><p><strong>Compile</strong> - Compile the current code to a .oso file for rendering</p><ul><li><p>When you select this option it will ask if you want to overwrite your file or save as an edit copy, the edit copy has an appended .edit in the name</p></li><li><p>The .oso compiled file is required for rendering</p></li></ul><p><br/><strong>Reload Source File</strong> - External edits to the file can be loaded from the saved/updated .osl file</p><p>The plus and minus icons are to expand and shrink the editor area.</p><p>The Parameters rollout will populate given a correct .oso file.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541164/rfm_PxrOSLexampleParameters.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=481&amp;height=876\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541164/rfm_PxrOSLexampleParameters.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"876\" data-width=\"481\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544541184\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfm_PxrOSLexampleParameters.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541164\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"ae1bb4bc-6fa3-47bf-bd3c-12cb2bd5fbf7\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541164/rfm_PxrOSLexampleParameters.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=481&amp;height=876 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541164/rfm_PxrOSLexampleParameters.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431568001&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=481&amp;height=876 1x\"></span><h3 id=\"UsingPxrOSL-UsingCustomOSLPatterns\">Using Custom OSL Patterns</h3><p>To begin, take a look at the page on <a href=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544541146/Installing+Custom+Nodes\" rel=\"nofollow\">Installing Custom Nodes</a>.</p><p>Define the RFM_SHOW_PATH environment variable to point to your own custom configuration directory.</p><p>Create a config directory in that new location and save a custom rfm.json file (you can copy the original one to make changes). Here's a simple version:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"21ab706e-9072-4741-a5b4-09d2352ee884\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">{\n    &quot;$schema&quot;: &quot;./rfmSchema.json&quot;,\n    &quot;resources&quot;: {\n        &quot;user&quot;: {\n            &quot;nodes&quot;: {\n                &quot;search_paths&quot;: [&quot;/Users/Artist/Shading/OSL_pkg/shader/myshow&quot;]\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n</div></div><p>You should have the following structure:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"19c68605-b227-4298-8bc1-82d8ea8333b8\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">RFM_SHOW_PATH\n   |_ config\n      |_ rfm.json</pre>\n</div></div><p>Now add some metadata to your OSL shaders (below we use a simple example):</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"5968ab7b-a494-495f-a100-00079967fb0d\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">//\n// AddFloat_1\n//\nshader AddFloat_1\n[[\n    string category = &quot;math&quot;,\n    string help = &quot;Adds two float inputs&quot;,\n    int rfm_nodeid = 1553001,\n    string rfm_classification = &quot;rendernode/RenderMan/pattern/Studio/math&quot;\n]]\n(\n    float input_A = .0,\n    float input_B = .0,\n    output float resultF = .0 [[ string widget=&quot;null&quot; ]],\n)\n{\n    resultF = input_A + input_B;\n}</pre>\n</div></div><p>Here are the parts of the Help data:</p><ul><li><p><strong>category </strong>- we classify this as a &quot;math&quot; node category</p></li><li><p><strong>help</strong> - Useful data for the user, a description basically.</p></li><li><p><strong>rfm_nodeid</strong> - is a unique ID for the node, Autodesk typically assigns these in a block. This is required to prevent clashes.</p></li><li><p><strong>rfm_classification</strong> - is the classification for the UI/Viewport that 'shader' objects must use under 'rendernode/RenderMan/pattern/' to be handled</p></li></ul><p />"
    }
  },
